<MainLayout title="Writing | Corrine J Blackthorn">
<section><div class="container"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">Writing</span><h1>Writing is how I make sense of the world.</h1><p>I write to help people see, understand, question, connect, and feel less alone. Sometimes that takes the form of essays, sometimes memoir, sometimes technical writing, and sometimes stories.</p></div><div class="grid"><article class="card"><h3>All of Me</h3><p>A memoir in progress about identity, survival, resilience, honesty, and becoming whole.</p><a class="button" href={links.ventures.blackthornFieldNotes}>Updates</a></article><article class="card"><h3>Blackthorn Field Notes</h3><p>Essays, reflections, technical notes, advocacy writing, observations, and long-form work.</p><a class="button" href={links.ventures.blackthornFieldNotes}>Visit</a></article><article class="card"><h3>KDP Publications</h3><p>Current and future books will be listed here as they are published.</p><a class="button" href="/writing/">Coming Soon</a></article></div></div></section><section class="quote-band"><div class="container"><blockquote>I write what people need to see and understand.</blockquote></div></section><section><div class="container"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">Influences</span><h2>Writers who shaped me.</h2><p>Chuck Palahniuk, Janet Evanovich, Kevin Mitnick, and Dan Brown each influenced different aspects of how I think about storytelling, pacing, curiosity, and communication.</p></div></div></section></MainLayout>